review_blob: pours hazy orange with a slightly pinkish hue. orange creamsicle aroma. taste is grapefruit membrane, straight up. finish is dry and tart.

pours black with a thick cream colored head and some lacing. the head stays put on this one, very impressive. black licorice and currant aroma. taste has notes of licorice, anise, currant, mint and other underripe berries. finish is dull and tart.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #5 - Three-Eyed Raven

review_blob: pours hazy golden with a fizzy white head and no lacing. bitter orange and butterscotch aroma. taste has notes of crayon wax, bitter orange, some serious minerality. the bitterness is strong but dull. finish is long but obtuse.
Very tart aroma, with orange and plum notes. Taste is very tart with notes of juicy orange, grapefruit, white plum and strawberries. Finish is toasty and acidic.
beer_name: BFM Abbaye de Saint Bon-Chien Grand Cru (2014) - Frenchy Sparkling Wine

review_blob: Cranberry and apple aroma. Taste has noted of bitter berries, vanilla, wood and tart cherry. Finish is bitter cherry with a boozy afterglow.

pours black with a thick, lasting tan head and dense lacing that coats the glass. fruity aroma with notes of cassis and fig. taste is rich with big sour fruit and licorice. finish is sour and dry. A very unique take on the imperial stout.
beer_name: Jester King Black Metal Farmhouse Imperial Stout

review_blob: pours dark brown with a lasting white head and some lacing. cedar and cherry aroma with hints of bitter chocolate. taste has notes of coffee, cedar, prune, nuts and cocoa. finish is bitter and woody.
pours pale amber with a thin white head and some lacing. toasty sweet tart aroma. taste has notes of toast, tart fruit, some candy sweetness, underripe berries. finish is crisp.

pours brown with a thin off white head. cold coffee, molasses and nutmeg aroma. taste is quite toasty and has notes of bitter chocolate, cold coffee, and some wet leaves. finish is bitter but with some desserty richness.
Drank at room temperature. Big juicy orange and flower aroma. Taste has notes of orange peel, pepper, grapefruit, caramel. Long bitter finish with fruit lingering.
beer_name: Great Lakes Rye of the Tiger

review_blob: Vanilla, cream and white chocolate aroma. Taste has notes of bourbon, vanilla. Finish burns.

pours black with a lasting tan head. smells like a happy old home with apple pie baking. lots of wood, must and apple sweetness. taste has notes of calvados, applewood, cocoa, and coffee. finish is fairly long with bitterness revealing itself later.

pours inky black with a foamy tan head and lots of lacing. aroma has notes of caramel, oak, butterscotch, crispy bacon, and soil. taste has notes of charred meat, oatmeal, bourbon, oak, bitter chocolate and anise. alcohol is very present throughout but mostly through the long finish. this beer does not seem to stop. outstanding.
Cayenne pepper and butter aroma. Taste has notes of tart blackberry and over ripe peaches. High acidity. Finish is tart, underripe cherries.
citrus rind aroma with tart berry notes. taste has grassy notes with lemon and grapefruit. finish is bitter and a tad juicy. the breadyness from the yeast is subtle but present.

pours very dark brown with lasting beige head and dense lacing. aroma is sweet, woody, chocolaty and bourbontastic. This beer is pulling no punches. taste has notes of wood, wood and wood with vanilla, chocolate, cocoa powder, bourbon, and some wood. finish is sticky sweey and boozy as hell. alcohol is prominent throughout. Probably the best Texas beer Ive yet had.
Pours black with a light brown head. Big beautiful chocolate and pepper aroma. Taste has chocolate, coffee, cream and bourbon in excellent balance. Finish is long and rich.
Pours pale with a thick, lasting head and some lacing. Floral citrus aroma. Light body for a saison with a lot of minerality. Finish is crisp. The best gluten free beer I've yet had.

pours a hazy, pale, metallic yellow. aroma has notes of marzipan, passion fruit, vanilla, honeysuckle and almond. taste has notes of gypsum, underripe apple, underipe pear, dried hops, dried vegetables. finish is stiff with dried orange peel, dried lemon peel and minerals. a light crisp beer reminiscent of Holsts piece. plenty of character with a pleasant sweetness and a quick taper.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Mercury - The Winged Messenger

review_blob: (2 years old) aroma similar to a viognier or albarino. green apple and melon predominates. sour grape, plum and apple in the taste. finish is a bit smokey with lots of sour cherry. tasty and refreshing.
beer_name: Jolly Pumpkin Fuego del Otono (Autumn Fire)

review_blob: peachy, sour aroma with lemon and spices. taste is sour orange and pumpkin, finish has a citric bite.
beer_name: Jolly Pumpkin La Parcela No. 1 Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: pours hazy yellow with a thin white head. aroma has light citrus and mineral notes. taste is overwhelmingly soapy and metallic. Theres sour fruit to be found but the off flavors are distracting. finish is soap and minerals. Weird.
Aroma is stiff and hoppy with a touch of malty sweetness. Taste has dried red fruit notes with some vegetal qualities. Finish is boozy.
Pours black with a thin tan head. Aroma has notes of butterscotch, cashew, chocolate, bourbon and overripe raspberry. Taste has notes of light red wine, overripe cherry. Finish is sweet.
UPDATED: JAN 22, 2015
Fresh, crisp aroma with strawberry notes. Big juicy tart berry taste well balanced by a strong malt presence. Finish is tart .
Big pumpkin and rum aroma. Taste has notes of pumpkin , vanilla , white wine . Finish is burning alcohol .
beer_name: Southern Tier Rum Barrel Aged Pumking

review_blob: UPDATED: JAN 10, 2015
beer_name: Hangar 24 Barrel Roll No. 03: Pugachevs Cobra - Barrel-Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: Dark cherry and plum aroma . Taste has notes of black currant, lavender, leather. Finish is sweet.
Wet wool and chocolate aroma. Light red wine taste with hints of smoke. Finish is oddly fruity.
Floral, spicy, melon notes in the aroma. Vanilla, white peppercorn, citrus taste. Minerals finish .

pours golden with a thin white head. tart, fruity aroma with tropical fruit notes and vanilla. taste has notes of tart, tropical fruit, vanilla and stone fruit. syrupy mouthfeel. finish is under-ripe apricot and vanilla. The dichotomy of the vanilla and the fruit is an odd one in this case and the balance is somewhat off.
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Venus - The Bringer Of Peace

review_blob: Big sweet coffee chocolate aroma. Taste is huge with coffee vanilla, butter scotch, and toffee. Finish is sticky and boozy . Amazing
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Coffee

review_blob: Aroma is underripe tropical fruit, herbs and vanilla. Mouthfeel is crisp. Taste has notes of mango, white tea, white peppercorn, cream and white plum. Finish is yeasty.
Stiff citric aroma with pine, grapefruit peel and fresh laundry. Taste has notes of grapefruit , white grape , flowers, ammonia. Finish is bitter. An ok ipa

ours a hazy straw color with a lasting thin white head and some lacing. honeydew and maple aroma with candy sugar. taste has notes of honey, lime, white peppercorn, pear, chamomile and toast. finish is citric, juicy and surprisingly long for a pils. lovely.
pours hazy pale golden with a very thin white head and no lacing. damp, musty lemon aroma. taste has notes of sour lemon drop, wet leaves, underripe apple and pineapple. finish is light and tart.
pours clear brown with a red glow. chocolate, cherry and wood aroma. taste has notes of cocoa, tree bark, raisins and cherry. finish is woody and stiff. A classic porter.

Aroma- Cranberry, peach, vodka. Taste- Apricot, sugar, maple, golden raisins. Finish- so strong with booze that any other notes are over taken. This beer has to be drank between cellar and room temperature to be palatable in my opinion.
Aroma- Rich vanilla, overripe fruit, smoked meat. Taste- smoked meat, fig, grape, apple, apricot. long fruity finish. Almost too much going on here but a formidable beer nonetheless.
UPDATED: JAN 22, 2015

pours pale golden with some lacing and a fizzy white head. lemon, passion fruit and cream aroma. taste has notes of lemon peel, vanilla, and white peppercorn with a significant dose of minerality. finish is sour.
pours hazy pale lime juice color. floral aroma with notes of sour lime, sour cranberry, sour apple and peach. taste is tart but juicy with lots of lime, and coriander. finish is medium. quite lovely.

pours golden with a lasting white head and some lacing. aroma is toasted brioche, golden raisin, and honey. taste is rich with light roast coffee, oak, toasted marshmallow, roasted pear and white chocolate. finish is long and biting.
beer_name: Stone Stochasticity Project Master of Disguise

review_blob: pours a clear reddish brown with a thin white head and some lacing. aroma has notes of burnt corn, caramel and vanilla. taste is much the same. finish is slightly acidic and malty. a very normal beer.
Coffee aroma with some dark fruit aromas. Taste has coffee notes and toasted dark fruit. Finish is damp coffee grounds.

pours dark and opaque with a thick, lasting cream colored head and lots of lacing. plum, underripe cherry and fig aromas with some grape soda and medicinal notes. taste is rich with dark plums, blackberry, leather, quince paste, rubber and nutmeg. finish is alcoholic and a bit hot. A lovely beer but no Westvleteren or Rochefort.

pours clear amber with a thin white head and minimal lacing. very light aroma with notes of caramel and oranges. taste has notes of caramel, oranges, orange peel, and butterscotch. The finish is toasty with hints of malted milk balls. a pleasant and easy beer but nothing impressive or memorable.
beer_name: Anchor Zymaster Series No. 6 Saaremaa Island Ale

review_blob: pours deep golden-orange with a wispy white head and some spotty lacing. aroma is oranges and minerals. taste has notes of vanilla, oranges, some wood and a large mineral presence. finish is more minerality and citrus with a noticeable alcohol burn. a lovely and enjoyable beer held back only by its dustiness.
Pours black with a thin beige head and some lacing. Aroma has notes of coffee and chocolate. Taste is strong with coffee and toast. Finish is lactic and a touch sweet.
